HEADWORD: Nodated
<hw>No"da*ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nodatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>nodare</ets> to make knotty, fr.
<ets>nodus</ets> knot. See <er>Node</er>.]</ety> <def>Knotted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Nodated hyperbola</b></col> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>, <cd>a
certain curve of the third order having two branches which cross each
other, forming a node.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nodation</ent>⟦br⟧
